Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Import errors for pandas or matplotlib

Solution: Ensure virtual environment is activated: source venv/bin/activate
Reinstall packages: pip install --upgrade pandas matplotlib seaborn
Issue: Division by zero in calculations

Solution: Add conditional checks before division operations
Example: result = numerator / denominator if denominator != 0 else 0
Issue: Visualization not displaying

Solution: Use plt.savefig() instead of plt.show() in headless environments
Check file permissions in visualizations directory
Issue: JSON serialization errors

Solution: Convert numpy types to Python native types
Example: float(numpy_value) or int(numpy_value)
Issue: Statistical calculations returning NaN

Solution: Check for missing data in CSV file
Use data.dropna() or data.fillna() to handle missing values
